# .NET / C# GitIgnore file

## Build Artifacts ##
# Folders containing compiled binaries and intermediate files
**/[Bb]in/
**/[Oo]bj/

# Build results
[Bb]uild/
[Rr]elease/
[Dd]ebug/
[Tt]est[Rr]esult*/

# NuGet Packages
# Ignore NuGet packages folder (older style)
**/[Pp]ackages/
# Ignore NuGet packages lock file (can cause merge conflicts, optional - uncomment if needed)
# **/packages.lock.json
# NuGet v3 package cache
.nuget/
# Ignore generated NuGet packages
*.nupkg
# Ignore symbol packages
*.snupkg
# Ignore temporary files during NuGet package installation
*.nuget.props
*.nuget.targets

## IDE Specific / User Settings ##
# Visual Studio specific
.vs/
*.suo
*.user
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates
*.sln.dotsettings.user # ReSharper settings
*.DotSettings.user    # Rider settings

# Visual Studio Code specific
.vscode/      # Can contain user-specific launch/tasks, review if you have shared settings
*.code-workspace

# Rider specific
.idea/

# User-specific files generated by other tools (e.g., CodeMaid)
*.docstates

## Environment Specific / Secrets ##
# Generally avoid committing environment-specific or secret files
# If you use User Secrets (recommended), the secrets file is typically outside the repo anyway.
# Consider adding specific files like appsettings.Development.json if they contain secrets
# *.secrets.json
# appsettings.*.json

# Publishing Profile settings (often contain local paths or sensitive info)
*.Publish.xml
*.pubxml
*.publishsettings
*.deployment.json

## Testing and Coverage ##
# Test results files
*.trx
# Coverage reports
*.cover
*.coverprofile
*.coverage
*.coveragexml
coverage.*

## Miscellaneous ##
# Various temporary files
*.log
*.log? # Handles log.1, log.2 etc.
*.tmp
*.bak
*.swp
*~

# OS generated files
# Windows
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
[Dd]esktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/

# MacOS
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

# Linux
.directory

# Log files from specific tools (e.g., NLog, Serilog - adjust patterns if needed)
# logs/
# App_Data/*.log

# Environment files (often contain secrets or local settings)
.env

# If you use LocalDB/SQL Express for development, ignore database files
*.mdf
*.ldf
*.sdf